The paper focuses on inter-cell interference coordination (ICIC) techniques in heterogeneous network (HetNet) deployments, which are related to network optimization and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses Reinforcement Learning (RL) techniques to optimize the network performance, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information theory and optimization, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses simulations to validate the proposed approaches, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
